<subSubSection lastPageId="11" lastPageNumber="210" pageId="10" pageNumber="209" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="10.[151,1436,1807,2012]" lastBlockId="11.[151,1436,151,248]" lastPageId="11" lastPageNumber="210" pageId="10" pageNumber="209">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,441,1807,1832]" pageId="10" pageNumber="209">Diagnostic features:</emphasis>
Face yellow; frons yellow with a Y-shaped black mark medially (
<figureCitation box="[1224,1294,1807,1832]" captionStart="FIGURE 5" captionStartId="10.[151,249,1740,1762]" captionTargetBox="[151,1434,414,1714]" captionTargetId="figure@10.[151,1436,411,1719]" captionTargetPageId="10" captionText="FIGURE 5. Platypygus chrysanthemi female syntype: a — lateral view, b — dorsal view, c — dorsolateral view of mesonotum." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/248554/files/figure.png" pageId="10" pageNumber="209">
Fig. 
<number box="[1280,1294,1807,1832]" pageId="10" pageNumber="209" value="5.0">5</number>
</figureCitation>
b); antennae completely black; occiput black except small posteriorly extended genal process yellow (
<figureCitation box="[1186,1256,1843,1868]" captionStart="FIGURE 5" captionStartId="10.[151,249,1740,1762]" captionTargetBox="[151,1434,414,1714]" captionTargetId="figure@10.[151,1436,411,1719]" captionTargetPageId="10" captionText="FIGURE 5. Platypygus chrysanthemi female syntype: a — lateral view, b — dorsal view, c — dorsolateral view of mesonotum." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/248554/files/figure.png" pageId="10" pageNumber="209">
Fig. 
<number box="[1242,1256,1843,1868]" pageId="10" pageNumber="209" value="5.0">5</number>
</figureCitation>
a, b); pronotum yellow with black stripe dorsomedially as continuation of median mesonotal stripe (
<figureCitation box="[1133,1203,1879,1904]" captionStart="FIGURE 5" captionStartId="10.[151,249,1740,1762]" captionTargetBox="[151,1434,414,1714]" captionTargetId="figure@10.[151,1436,411,1719]" captionTargetPageId="10" captionText="FIGURE 5. Platypygus chrysanthemi female syntype: a — lateral view, b — dorsal view, c — dorsolateral view of mesonotum." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/248554/files/figure.png" pageId="10" pageNumber="209">
Fig. 
<number box="[1189,1203,1879,1904]" pageId="10" pageNumber="209" value="5.0">5</number>
</figureCitation>
b); mesonotum with dense long and black hairs, with three black stripes, lateral stripes extend from posterior margin of postpronotal lobes to postalar calli, median stripe extends from anterior margin of mesonotum to scutellum (
<figureCitation box="[1222,1289,1951,1976]" captionStart="FIGURE 5" captionStartId="10.[151,249,1740,1762]" captionTargetBox="[151,1434,414,1714]" captionTargetId="figure@10.[151,1436,411,1719]" captionTargetPageId="10" captionText="FIGURE 5. Platypygus chrysanthemi female syntype: a — lateral view, b — dorsal view, c — dorsolateral view of mesonotum." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/248554/files/figure.png" pageId="10" pageNumber="209">
Fig. 
<number box="[1275,1289,1951,1976]" pageId="10" pageNumber="209" value="5.0">5</number>
</figureCitation>
b); scutellum almost all yellow with a semicircular black mark basally; lateral black spot on mesonotum coalesced with lateral stripe (
<figureCitation box="[231,302,151,176]" captionStart="FIGURE 5" captionStartId="10.[151,249,1740,1762]" captionTargetBox="[151,1434,414,1714]" captionTargetId="figure@10.[151,1436,411,1719]" captionTargetPageId="10" captionText="FIGURE 5. Platypygus chrysanthemi female syntype: a — lateral view, b — dorsal view, c — dorsolateral view of mesonotum." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/248554/files/figure.png" pageId="11" pageNumber="210">
Fig. 
<number box="[287,302,151,176]" pageId="11" pageNumber="210" value="5.0">5</number>
</figureCitation>
c); postpronotal lobes and postalar calli yellow; pleura yellow except lower part of katepisternum, meron, and spot on dorsal margin of anepisternum black; halter stem and knob yellow; r-m crossvein at about middle of cell dm, cell br longer than cell bm.
</paragraph>
