<subSubSection pageId="11" pageNumber="210" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="11.[151,1436,1763,2004]" pageId="11" pageNumber="210">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,315,1799,1824]" pageId="11" pageNumber="210">Remarks.</emphasis>
Theodor (
<number box="[435,493,1800,1824]" pageId="11" pageNumber="210" value="1983.0">1983</number>
) illustrated the male and female genitalia of 
<taxonomicName box="[1007,1188,1799,1824]" class="Insecta" family="Bombyliidae" genus="Platypygus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="11" pageNumber="210" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="chrysanthemi">
<emphasis box="[1007,1188,1799,1824]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="210">P. chrysanthemi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. Based on the female genitalia (
<figureCitation box="[266,337,1835,1860]" captionStart="FIGURE 6" captionStartId="11.[151,249,1702,1724]" captionTargetBox="[167,1421,312,1671]" captionTargetId="figure@11.[151,1436,301,1681]" captionTargetPageId="11" captionText="FIGURE 6. Female genitalia of Platypygus chrysanthemi: a — furca and ducts, b — spermathecal reservoir." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/248555/files/figure.png" pageId="11" pageNumber="210">
Fig. 
<number box="[322,337,1835,1860]" pageId="11" pageNumber="210" value="6.0">6</number>
</figureCitation>
) this species belongs to the group of species having two sclerites lateral to the genital orifice, which includes 
<taxonomicName box="[335,610,1871,1896]" class="Insecta" family="Bombyliidae" genus="Platypygus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="11" pageNumber="210" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="titanomedea">
<emphasis box="[335,610,1871,1896]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="210">Platypygus titanomedea</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName box="[672,835,1872,1895]" class="Insecta" family="Bombyliidae" genus="Platypygus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="11" pageNumber="210" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="americanus">
<emphasis box="[672,835,1872,1895]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="210">P. americanus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. The spermathecal reservoir (
<figureCitation box="[1187,1257,1871,1896]" captionStart="FIGURE 6" captionStartId="11.[151,249,1702,1724]" captionTargetBox="[167,1421,312,1671]" captionTargetId="figure@11.[151,1436,301,1681]" captionTargetPageId="11" captionText="FIGURE 6. Female genitalia of Platypygus chrysanthemi: a — furca and ducts, b — spermathecal reservoir." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/248555/files/figure.png" pageId="11" pageNumber="210">
Fig. 
<number box="[1243,1257,1871,1896]" pageId="11" pageNumber="210" value="6.0">6</number>
</figureCitation>
b) is somewhat similar in shape to 
<taxonomicName box="[364,530,1907,1932]" class="Insecta" family="Bombyliidae" genus="Platypygus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="11" pageNumber="210" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="titanomedea">
<emphasis box="[364,530,1907,1932]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="210">P. titanomedea</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. In the male genitalia illustrated by Theodor (Figs. 
<number box="[1106,1179,1907,1932]" pageId="11" pageNumber="210" value="58.5" valueMax="59.0" valueMin="58.0">58–59</number>
, page 
<number box="[1250,1281,1908,1932]" pageId="11" pageNumber="210" value="32.0">32</number>
), the shape of the gonostylus and gonocoxa is somewhat similar to 
<taxonomicName box="[745,882,1943,1968]" class="Insecta" family="Bombyliidae" genus="Platypygus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="11" pageNumber="210" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="kurdorum">
<emphasis box="[745,882,1943,1968]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="210">P. kurdorum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<figureCitation box="[898,964,1943,1968]" captionStart="FIGURE 8" captionStartId="14.[151,249,1976,1998]" captionTargetBox="[171,1409,209,1925]" captionTargetId="figure@14.[171,1417,193,1954]" captionTargetPageId="14" captionText="FIGURE 8. Genitalia of Platypygus kurdorum: a — epandrium (lateral view), b — gonocoxites (dorsal view), c — phallic complex (dorsal view), d — phallic complex (lateral view), e — female genitalia (furca and tubes), f — spermathecal reservoir." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/248557/files/figure.png" pageId="11" pageNumber="210">
Fig. 
<number box="[951,964,1943,1968]" pageId="11" pageNumber="210" value="8.0">8</number>
</figureCitation>
b) but the presence of vanes at the base of basal aedeagal apodeme is a distinct difference (Fig. 
<number box="[743,774,1979,2004]" pageId="11" pageNumber="210" value="59.0">59</number>
, page 
<number box="[845,877,1980,2004]" pageId="11" pageNumber="210" value="32.0">32</number>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
